 ${misc:Depends},
 ${python3:Depends},
Description: Hugging Face diffusion pipelines for image and audio
 diffusers from Hugging Face wraps pretrained diffusion pipelines
 (Stable Diffusion, AudioLDM, and many more) behind a uniform Python
 API and exposes the lower-level UNet / VAE / scheduler components
 for custom training and inference. Avalan ships it in its `vendors`
 extras at `>= 0.37.1, < 0.38`; the rebuild lands at 0.37.1.
 .
 The heavy ML runtime dependencies (torch, accelerate, transformers,
 jax, etc.) are intentionally not declared here -- diffusers's
 install_requires is the minimal interface set (Pillow, numpy,
 huggingface-hub, safetensors, regex, requests, httpx, filelock,
 importlib_metadata), and per Avalan's APT.md heavyweight extras
 stay out of the apt-installed package. Callers who need accelerate
 or torch install them with pip into a user-controlled venv on top
 of the system install.
